Let's go.

1176
01:26:17,929 --> 01:26:20,045
Now, what the hell were you
guys waiting for?

1177
01:26:20,249 --> 01:26:23,639
What do you m--?
Mean, boy?

1178
01:26:25,209 --> 01:26:28,406
Those lovers were trying
to kill us back there.

1179
01:26:30,369 --> 01:26:31,802
Change.

1180
01:26:32,689 --> 01:26:35,249
Change? What do you mean, "change"?

1181
01:26:35,969 --> 01:26:37,004
You can't do that!

1182
01:26:37,209 --> 01:26:40,201
It's all right, major.
We're gonna change back later.

1183
01:26:40,729 --> 01:26:42,606
They can't stop us now.

1184
01:26:43,089 --> 01:26:44,363
Let's go.

1185
01:26:44,889 --> 01:26:46,527
Come on.

1186
01:26:47,529 --> 01:26:48,518
We're on our way.

1187
01:26:58,729 --> 01:27:01,038
We get across this road, take 10.

1188
01:27:09,489 --> 01:27:11,161
What are we waiting here for?

1189
01:27:11,569 --> 01:27:14,083
For a jeep, a heavy machine gun
and four men.

1190
01:27:17,089 --> 01:27:18,204
Like this one?

1191
01:27:18,969 --> 01:27:19,958
Slow down.

1192
01:27:20,649 --> 01:27:22,048
Ten-hut!

1193
01:27:29,409 --> 01:27:30,888
Good afternoon, general.

1194
01:27:40,209 --> 01:27:41,847
The Mafia has landed!

1195
01:27:42,049 --> 01:27:44,085
-Whatever Franko says, Franko does!
-Machine gun.

1196
01:27:44,289 --> 01:27:45,927
Let's get it out. Move it out.

1197
01:27:46,129 --> 01:27:47,960
-Come on, snap it up.
-Franko, out!

1198
01:27:48,489 --> 01:27:50,366
Out? What do you mean, "out"?

1199
01:27:50,529 --> 01:27:53,407
-Who do you think stole this thing?
-You did, my boy.

1200
01:27:53,889 --> 01:27:57,962
Look, you and Pinkley are the only guys
that Colonel Breed got a good look at.

1201
01:27:58,209 --> 01:28:01,087
This operation is a big enough risk
without you coming along.

1202
01:28:01,249 --> 01:28:03,444
-Out.
-Come on, Franko.

1203
01:28:04,929 --> 01:28:07,727
Jefferson, you have until 0930
to show up with the ambulance.

1204
01:28:07,929 --> 01:28:10,045
You don't make it,
I'll figure you got nailed.

1205
01:28:10,209 --> 01:28:12,359
-Then we'll take a whack at plan B.
-Right.

1206
01:28:13,449 --> 01:28:15,121
So long, major.

1207
01:28:17,769 --> 01:28:19,964
Hold on, Maggott.
Don't want to lose you now.

1208
01:28:22,369 --> 01:28:24,325
Attention!

1209
01:28:25,649 --> 01:28:27,128
Attention.

1210
01:28:29,009 --> 01:28:29,998
Ten-hut!

1211
01:28:32,609 --> 01:28:34,839
-Morning, Breed.
-Morning. Quite a surprise.

1212
01:28:35,009 --> 01:28:37,887
-Everything under control?
-I think you could say that, sir.

1213
01:28:38,049 --> 01:28:40,802
Good, good.
At ease, gentlemen, at ease.

1214
01:28:41,009 --> 01:28:44,160
Just thought I'd drop by to see
how things are shaping up.

1215
01:28:44,449 --> 01:28:46,804
So this is what it looks like, huh?

1216
01:28:51,809 --> 01:28:53,686
Come on, push!

1217
01:28:57,129 --> 01:28:59,643
-Posey, remember, you're hurt.
-Oh, I'm dying.

1218
01:28:59,849 --> 01:29:00,964
Come on, Maggott.

1219
01:29:03,329 --> 01:29:04,842
Stand back, now.

1220
01:29:14,609 --> 01:29:16,645
-What's that?
-Over there!

1221
01:29:18,649 --> 01:29:21,880
-What was that?
-Down the road, sir. See that smoke?

1222
01:29:22,129 --> 01:29:24,882
-Sergeant, have somebody take a look.
-Yes, sir.

1223
01:29:25,089 --> 01:29:28,240
-What are they doing around that ridge?
-I don't know, sir.

1224
01:29:28,449 --> 01:29:31,725
That should've been cleared
half an hour ago.

1225
01:29:31,929 --> 01:29:35,080
Now, colonel, it sure doesn't look like
it's been cleared, does it?

1226
01:29:35,249 --> 01:29:36,238
Let's go.

1227
01:29:40,929 --> 01:29:44,285
-Posey, remember, you're injured.
-Gilpin, you forgot the ketchup.

1228
01:29:44,449 --> 01:29:46,280
-Help!
-Come on.

1229
01:30:01,849 --> 01:30:03,441
Sir?

1230
01:30:06,049 --> 01:30:08,927
We got a man that's hurt bad.
We'd like to call an ambulance.

1231
01:30:09,089 --> 01:30:10,966
Call an ambulance.
Go see what happened.

1232
01:30:11,129 --> 01:30:13,848
-Yes, sir. Come on, you two.
-Private?

1233
01:30:14,209 --> 01:30:16,165
-Come here.
-Yes, sir.

1234
01:30:16,369 --> 01:30:17,961
What were you doing on that road?

1235
01:30:18,169 --> 01:30:20,285
Our jeep got a flat tire.
We went into a ditch.

1236
01:30:21,329 --> 01:30:25,083
I didn't ask you that. I asked you
what you were doing on that road.

1237
01:30:25,249 --> 01:30:27,319
Spotting for the Field Artillery, sir.

1238
01:30:32,009 --> 01:30:33,044
Let's see that map.

1239
01:30:33,209 --> 01:30:34,688
Move Able, Charlie Company to. . .

1240
01:30:34,889 --> 01:30:36,686
. . .the bridge under smoke screen.

1241
01:30:36,889 --> 01:30:40,928
Baker Company bank towards
the ridge at 1420 hours.

1242
01:30:41,089 --> 01:30:44,286
-Private. Come here.
-Yes, sir.

1243
01:30:46,489 --> 01:30:47,842
What's your name and outfit?

1244
01:30:48,049 --> 01:30:49,448
Private Matthew Donald, sir.

1245
01:30:49,649 --> 01:30:54,439
Serial number 726256.
Battery B, 526th Field Artillery, sir.

1246
01:30:54,649 --> 01:30:57,527
-Where are your orders?
-Right here, sir.

1247
01:30:59,089 --> 01:31:01,239
From Captain Thornhill, sir.

1248
01:31:04,129 --> 01:31:06,848
I know most of the men
under my command.

1249
01:31:08,129 --> 01:31:09,960
But I don't recall seeing you before.

1250
01:31:10,329 --> 01:31:13,127
No, sir.
I was transferred in last week, sir.

1251
01:31:17,169 --> 01:31:21,048
We're getting congested at point B.
Two forces have mined the road.

1252
01:31:21,209 --> 01:31:22,722
-Where's Peterson?
-Here it comes!

1253
01:31:27,169 --> 01:31:28,761
Clear the way!

1254
01:31:29,169 --> 01:31:30,522
Looks like somebody got hurt.

1255
01:31:33,569 --> 01:31:35,082
Watch it there!

1256
01:31:36,289 --> 01:31:38,678
Okay, let's have some help
with this soldier.

1257
01:31:40,209 --> 01:31:43,281
Count of three, lift. One, two, lift.

1258
01:31:44,609 --> 01:31:46,042
Take it easy now.

1259
01:31:48,409 --> 01:31:51,162
-Where do we put him, sir?
-Put him there.

1260
01:31:53,809 --> 01:31:57,279
-You can stay, but keep out of the way.
-Yes, sir. Thank you, sir.

1261
01:32:25,409 --> 01:32:27,877
Sorry, but this is the end
of the line for you.

1262
01:32:28,089 --> 01:32:30,159
But we got a bad accident
down here, sir.

1263
01:32:30,369 --> 01:32:34,123
That's too bad, because you just
became prisoners of war.

1264
01:32:37,969 --> 01:32:39,163
It's the enemy, sir!

1265
01:32:39,449 --> 01:32:41,201
All right, come on, let's go.

1266
01:32:42,529 --> 01:32:44,201
Let's go, let's go.

1267
01:32:46,249 --> 01:32:47,841
They can't do that.

1268
01:32:50,449 --> 01:32:52,041
You're wearing Red Force insignia.

1269
01:32:52,569 --> 01:32:54,799
That's right. We're traitors.

1270
01:32:54,969 --> 01:32:57,403
-Watch my finger.
-They use real bullets, you idiot!

1271
01:32:57,609 --> 01:32:59,361
Now, look here, I'm a doctor, major.

1272
01:32:59,569 --> 01:33:01,764
And I'm a major, captain.

1273
01:33:01,969 --> 01:33:05,405
Yes, sir, but we had a radio message.
There's a man badly hurt down there.

1274
01:33:05,569 --> 01:33:06,558
Hurry it up!

1275
01:33:06,769 --> 01:33:09,408
Here's our permission to cross
all lines and roadblocks.

1276
01:33:10,009 --> 01:33:13,319
Very cute idea, captain.
But it won't work. Get out.

1277
01:33:13,689 --> 01:33:17,284
But it's not a gag, sir.
There's a real casualty there.

1278
01:33:17,489 --> 01:33:18,842
All set back here, Jefferson.

1279
01:33:19,049 --> 01:33:21,244
Sir, will you explain
the rules to him?

1280
01:33:21,449 --> 01:33:22,484
The man may be dying.

1281
01:33:22,689 --> 01:33:25,203
I'm just an observer, captain,
not an umpire.

1282
01:33:25,409 --> 01:33:27,877
I can't interfere
or make any rulings.

1283
01:33:28,449 --> 01:33:30,758
Come on, doc,
I've got a sick tree back here.

1284
01:33:30,969 --> 01:33:32,561
Come on, you too.

1285
01:33:32,769 --> 01:33:35,966
She's blond, she's engaged.
Come on, sugar!

1286
01:33:36,169 --> 01:33:39,161
-Got your bracelet right here.
-What's the matter?

1287
01:33:39,329 --> 01:33:41,763
Come on, Little Red Riding Hood.

1288
01:33:42,889 --> 01:33:44,527
You're really gonna enjoy this.

1289
01:33:47,169 --> 01:33:48,921
How about this patient, huh, doc?

1290
01:33:49,849 --> 01:33:51,999
You're really gonna enjoy it here, doc.

1291
01:33:52,169 --> 01:33:53,682
Come on, men. What about 0930?

1292
01:33:53,889 --> 01:33:56,608
All right, take out the blue bands.
Let's go!

1293
01:33:56,809 --> 01:33:58,208
Change to the blue armband!

1294
01:33:58,369 --> 01:33:59,484
What about the prisoners?

1295
01:33:59,689 --> 01:34:03,159
Sorry, major. We can't spare any men
to look after prisoners.

1296
01:34:03,729 --> 01:34:04,957
You coming?

1297
01:34:23,289 --> 01:34:25,723
-Is he trying to kill us?
-We must be going 120.

1298
01:34:25,929 --> 01:34:27,760
He's gonna squash us
in this sardine can.

1299
01:34:27,969 --> 01:34:30,324
You want to be there by 0930,
don't you?

1300
01:34:30,489 --> 01:34:31,968
Yeah.

1301
01:34:32,329 --> 01:34:36,242
--pulling back the map reference,
397492.

1302
01:34:36,449 --> 01:34:37,723
That's Blue Force crew.

1303
01:34:38,649 --> 01:34:41,641
Call in company orders and hit them
when they reach crossroads.

1304
01:34:41,849 --> 01:34:42,998
Hello, Able 3.

1305
01:34:43,209 --> 01:34:45,882
Don't worry, Bill. They called
for the ambulance.

1306
01:34:59,249 --> 01:35:02,047
-It's gonna be all right.
-Yes, it will.

1307
01:35:03,489 --> 01:35:05,241
It's gonna be all right.

1308
01:35:05,449 --> 01:35:09,203
I want a strike on Hill 80
between them at 1400 hours.

1309
01:35:09,369 --> 01:35:12,406
Move them up to the base of the hill
and keep their heads down.

1310
01:35:12,609 --> 01:35:17,080
Well, thanks very much, colonel.
It's been very instructive.

1311
01:35:17,249 --> 01:35:20,321
I think I'll take a little ride now
and get the overall picture.

1312
01:35:20,529 --> 01:35:22,201
Yes, sir, thank you.

1313
01:35:32,249 --> 01:35:34,046
Move it over. Give them room.

1314
01:36:13,369 --> 01:36:16,088
Forward observation report.
Blue Force tanks approaching. . .

1315
01:36:16,249 --> 01:36:18,046
. . .airfield at map reference--

1316
01:36:19,209 --> 01:36:20,528
Out of the way!

1317
01:36:22,569 --> 01:36:23,968
Out of the way!

1318
01:36:29,129 --> 01:36:30,767
Come on.
Watch out for the ambulance!

1319
01:36:39,649 --> 01:36:42,402
There he is. The old man.

1320
01:36:46,449 --> 01:36:47,962
Come on, observers!

1321
01:36:58,369 --> 01:37:00,200
Major Reisman's compliments, sir.

1322
01:37:08,529 --> 01:37:12,966
Hey, major. What do you think
about that one, major?

1323
01:37:13,129 --> 01:37:16,758
I didn't wanna tell you before because
I thought it might make you nervous.

1324
01:37:16,929 --> 01:37:19,966
After our last little party,
the generals were all in favor. . .

1325
01:37:20,169 --> 01:37:22,364
. . .of sending you back to finish
your sentences.

1326
01:37:22,569 --> 01:37:24,446
-Or get hung.
-Or get hung.

1327
01:37:24,609 --> 01:37:25,598
Or get hung.

1328
01:37:26,089 --> 01:37:27,920
But I made a deal with them.

1329
01:37:28,289 --> 01:37:32,168
Knocking off Breed's headquarters
is what got you guys off the hook.

1330
01:37:36,129 --> 01:37:38,120
You weren't really worried,
were you, major?

1331
01:37:38,329 --> 01:37:39,921
No, not much, he wasn't.

1332
01:37:40,129 --> 01:37:42,279
But we still have
one operation to go.

1333
01:37:42,489 --> 01:37:46,846
If you guys foul up on this one, none
of us will ever play the violin again.

1334
01:37:47,049 --> 01:37:49,199
Because up until now,
it's all been a game.

1335
01:37:49,369 --> 01:37:51,883
But as of tomorrow night,
it's gonna be the real thing.

1336
01:37:52,089 --> 01:37:54,080
If you want to know how real,
I'll tell you.

1337
01:37:54,289 --> 01:37:57,247
It's my guess the lot of you guys
won't be coming back.

1338
01:37:57,409 --> 01:37:59,445
But there's no sense in squawking
about that.

1339
01:37:59,609 --> 01:38:01,247
Because the Army never did love you.

1340
01:38:01,409 --> 01:38:03,206
Besides, you all volunteered, right?

1341
01:38:03,409 --> 01:38:06,048
-Yeah.
-Well, that's more than I did.

1342
01:38:06,929 --> 01:38:08,442
Sergeant Bowren.

1343
01:38:09,249 --> 01:38:11,717
Look, I know we've been over this
a thousand times. . .

1344
01:38:11,889 --> 01:38:14,687
. . .but a lot can go wrong.
We gotta be prepared to improvise.

1345
01:38:14,849 --> 01:38:17,727
So let's see what happens
if everything goes right. Ready?

1346
01:38:17,929 --> 01:38:20,602
-One.
-At the roadblock, we've just begun.

1347
01:38:20,809 --> 01:38:24,165
-One.
-At the roadblock, we've just begun.

1348
01:38:24,369 --> 01:38:26,564
-Two.
-The guards are through.

1349
01:38:26,769 --> 01:38:29,761
-Three.
-The major's men are on a spree.

1350
01:38:29,969 --> 01:38:32,961
-Four.
-Major and Wladislaw through the door.

1351
01:38:33,169 --> 01:38:36,525
-Five.
-Pinkley stays out in the drive.

1352
01:38:36,729 --> 01:38:39,960
-Six.
-The major gives the rope a fix.

1353
01:38:40,169 --> 01:38:43,241
-Seven.
-Wladislaw throws the hook to heaven.

1354
01:38:44,049 --> 01:38:47,325
-Eight.
-Jiminez has got a date.

1355
01:38:47,809 --> 01:38:51,324
-Nine.
-The other guys go up the line.

1356
01:38:52,089 --> 01:38:55,525
-Ten.
-Sawyer and Gilpin are in the pen.

1357
01:38:55,729 --> 01:38:58,880
-Eleven.
-Posey guards points five and seven.

1358
01:38:59,529 --> 01:39:03,317
-Twelve.
-Wladislaw and major go down to delve.

1359
01:39:03,849 --> 01:39:04,998
And where's Donald Duck?

1360
01:39:05,929 --> 01:39:08,489
Donald Duck's down at the crossroads
with a machine gun.

1361
01:39:08,889 --> 01:39:11,528
And he'd better not be asleep,
or we'll all be in trouble.

1362
01:39:13,409 --> 01:39:16,924
-Thirteen.
-Franko goes up without being seen.

1363
01:39:17,569 --> 01:39:19,525
-Fourteen.
-Zero hour.

1364
01:39:19,809 --> 01:39:22,448
-And?
-Mayonnaise cuts the cable. . .

1365
01:39:22,609 --> 01:39:24,327
. . .Franko cuts the phone.

1366
01:39:24,529 --> 01:39:26,087
-Fifteen.
-Franko goes in. . .

1367
01:39:26,249 --> 01:39:27,648
. . .where the others have been.

1368
01:39:28,049 --> 01:39:32,201
-Sixteen.
-We all come out like it's Halloween.

1369
01:39:33,729 --> 01:39:35,481
And kill every officer in sight.

1370
01:39:35,649 --> 01:39:37,002
Ours or theirs?

1371
01:39:37,169 --> 01:39:38,966
Well, let's start off with theirs, huh?

1372
01:39:39,169 --> 01:39:41,603
Let's take it again from the top,
without the ad-libs.

1373
01:39:41,809 --> 01:39:45,279
-All right, one.
-Down the roadblock, we've just begun.

1374
01:39:45,489 --> 01:39:48,287
-Two.
-The guards are through.

1375
01:39:48,449 --> 01:39:51,600
-Three.
-The major's men are on a spree.

1376
01:39:51,969 --> 01:39:54,358
-Fourteen.
-Zero hour.

1377
01:39:54,569 --> 01:39:57,322
-And?
-Mayonnaise cuts the cable. . .

1378
01:39:57,529 --> 01:39:59,167
. . .Franko cuts the phone.

1379
01:39:59,329 --> 01:40:01,206
-Fifteen.
-Franko goes in. . .

1380
01:40:01,369 --> 01:40:02,882
. . .where the others have been.

1381
01:40:03,329 --> 01:40:07,368
-Sixteen.
-We all come out like it's Halloween.

1382
01:40:07,569 --> 01:40:09,400
Seventeen?

1383
01:40:09,569 --> 01:40:12,288
Seventeen. D-day.

1384
01:40:12,809 --> 01:40:15,528
We get out as best we can
and make our way to the coast.

1385
01:40:16,249 --> 01:40:19,798
And hope that the entire invasion
hasn't been a total disaster.

1386
01:40:20,009 --> 01:40:22,204
Otherwise, we got a long swim home.

1387
01:40:22,769 --> 01:40:24,441
How much longer, major?

1388
01:40:24,609 --> 01:40:25,962
I'll ask the driver.

1389
01:40:32,689 --> 01:40:35,249
You're not worried about jumping
at night, are you?

1390
01:40:37,849 --> 01:40:39,282
Getting back.

1391
01:40:46,569 --> 01:40:47,558
Ready.

1392
01:40:52,289 --> 01:40:53,563
Cargo.

1393
01:41:04,449 --> 01:41:05,438
Go.

1394
01:41:20,289 --> 01:41:23,406
-Where have you been? We're late.
-We've been looking for Jiminez.

1395
01:41:23,729 --> 01:41:26,641
-And?
-We found him hung up in an apple tree.

1396
01:41:26,849 --> 01:41:29,488
-His neck's broken.
-You mean he's dead?

1397
01:41:29,689 --> 01:41:31,839
That's exactly what I mean.

1398
01:41:34,049 --> 01:41:35,243
-This far.
-Yeah.

1399
01:41:38,049 --> 01:41:41,439
All right, Franko, now you know why
we all checked out on that rope, huh?

1400
01:41:45,049 --> 01:41:46,528
Gilpin, number eight.

1401
01:41:46,729 --> 01:41:48,765
Gilpin, did you hear me?

1402
01:41:48,929 --> 01:41:51,397
-Eight.
-Gilpin's got a date?

1403
01:41:54,449 --> 01:41:56,440
-Fourteen.
-Zero hour.

1404
01:41:56,649 --> 01:41:58,799
-And?
-Gilpin cuts the cables. . .

1405
01:41:59,009 --> 01:42:01,284
-. . .Franko cuts the phone.
-Let's go.

1406
01:42:09,769 --> 01:42:13,284
-What a great way to start out, huh?
-Yeah.

1407
01:43:18,769 --> 01:43:20,566
So far, so good, major.

1408
01:44:22,289 --> 01:44:24,041
Where are those guys?

1409
01:44:26,449 --> 01:44:27,848
Here they come.

